Argentine Stocks: Banco Hipotecario, Banco Marco, Tenaris Gain

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-03-17T15:45:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/argentine-stocks-banco-hipotecario-banco-marco-tenaris-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:33 a.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 1.8 percent to 3,253.93.    Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)   gained 2.8 percent to 2.60
pesos, while  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN)   increased 1.6
percent to 15.45 pesos and  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   rose 1.5
percent to 16.50 pesos. The price of Argentine sovereign bonds
rose today, which signals higher value for banks’ fixed-income
holdings.    Tenaris SA (TEN)  , the world’s largest maker of seamless
steel tubes used in the oil and gas industries, rose 3 percent
to 94 pesos as  Japan  moved closer to restoring power at a
nuclear plant and Group of Seven officials said they will meet
tomorrow to discuss potential coordinated action to assist the
world’s third-largest economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  